<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2014]" box="[199,822,1089,1114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1090,1114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Female.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[452,555,1089,1113]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.80 mm</quantity>
; wing length: 
<quantity box="[714,818,1089,1113]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.65">2.65 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Head. Antenna dark yellow, first flagellomere about twice as long as wide; arista short pubescent with hairs shorter than basal width. Frons dark yellow. Face yellow-white, gena ventral to eye darker yellow; occiput dorsal fourth dark brown, ventral half yellow-white.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Thorax. Postpronotal lobe black-brown in anterior half, posteriorly with whitish crescent, extending to seta. Scutum ratio 
<number box="[301,339,1269,1293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="0.9">0.9</number>
; shining black-brown, silver microtrichia in typical pattern except more reduced than in other species (
<figureCitation box="[213,273,1305,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,749,772]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,334,725]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,323,725]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neoceratitis scutum, dorsal view: a) albiseta; b) flavoscutellata; c) lycii." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209665/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[263,273,1305,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
a); dark pilosity except where silver microtrichosity with silvery setulae. Pleura brown, anepisternum white except ventral margin; katatergite and anatergite whitish, posteroventral margin of laterotergite narrowly brown; one white anepisternal seta. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[682,748,1377,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1730,1753]" captionTargetBox="[157,1433,832,1697]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,821,1708]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neoceratitis scutellum, dorsal view: a) albiseta; b) asiatica; c) cyanescens; d) flavoscutellata; e) lycii." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209666/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[734,748,1377,1401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a) swollen with concave margin near basal seta; black brown, subbasally with whitish band, interrupted medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2014]" box="[199,883,1449,1474]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Legs. Mostly yellow; mid and hind femora yellowish-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Wing. With discal, subapical, anterior apical and posterior apical brown bands (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1181,1485,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1399,1422]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,237,1307]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neoceratitis wing: a) albiseta; b) asiatica; c) cyanescens; d) efflatouni; e) flavoscutellata; f) lycii." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209667/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1167,1181,1485,1509]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
a); all well developed. Basal brownish part largely consisting of partly confluent patches and streaks, separated from discal band in basal part of cell cu and apical part of cell bm; otherwise partly confluent through dark spots. Subapical band connected with discal and anterior apical bands. Anterior and posterior apical bands connected. R-M ratio 
<number box="[1222,1275,1593,1617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="0.95">0.95</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Abdomen. Shining black-brown. Tergites 
<number box="[678,692,1629,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[750,764,1629,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="4.0">4</number>
almost completely covered with silvery microtrichia, only narrow anterior margin with brownish microtrichia except tergite 
<number box="[897,911,1665,1689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="4.0">4</number>
where silvery microtrichia extends to anterior margin. Oviscape about half as long as abdominal tergites 
<number box="[842,879,1701,1725]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1-5</number>
jointly, shining black-brown. Aculeus (
<figureCitation box="[1344,1414,1701,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1832,1855]" captionTargetBox="[160,1417,590,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,575,1810]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Neoceratitis aculeus: a) albiseta; b) asiatica; c) cyanescens; d) efflatouni; e) lycii; f) flavoscutellata." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209669/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1400,1414,1701,1725]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a) orange, flattened; four times as long as wide; apically evenly tapered (
<figureCitation box="[936,1003,1737,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,193,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Neoceratitis aculeus tip: a) albiseta; b) asiatica; c) cyanescens; d) efflatouni; e) flavoscutellata; f) lycii." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209670/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[988,1003,1737,1761]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a), simply pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1017,2014]" box="[199,392,1773,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1773,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<collectingCountry box="[199,262,1773,1797]" name="Malta" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Male</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
